        <div n="327-001K" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-327-001K-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-327-001K-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-327-001K-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-327-001K-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-327-001K-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-327-001K-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-327-001K-line-1"> As Thomas was cudgeld one day by his wife,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-327-001K-line-2"> He took to his heels &amp; ran for his life,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-327-001K-line-3"> Toms three dearest friends came by in the Squabble,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-327-001K-line-4"> And Screen'd him at once f<hi rend="sup">m</hi> y<hi rend="sup">e</hi> Shrew &amp; the Rabble.</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-327-001K-line-5"> They ventur'd to give him some friendly advice,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-327-001K-line-6"> But Tom is a fellow of Humour so nice.</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-327-001K-line-7"> Too proud to take Council, too wise to take warning,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-327-001K-line-8"> He sent to all three, a Challenge next morning.</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-327-001K-line-9"> He fought w<hi rend="sup">th</hi> all three, thrice ventur'd his life,</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-327-001K-line-10"> Then went home again, &amp; was threshd by his wife.327-001K   </l></lg></div>
      </div>
